%% Adds the main heading for the SI text. Comment out this line if you do not have any supporting information text.
\SItext
This Supporting Information provides detailed tables and figures for the field experiment described in the main text, in which we randomly assigned over 15,000 vetted Wikipedia contributors across the Arabic, German, Persian, and Polish language editions to receive private thank-you messages from peer volunteers or to serve as controls. The main text reports that receiving thanks increased the rate at which participants thanked others, improved two-week retention, and raised daily labor hours---with the magnitude of labor-hour effects varying by pre-treatment activity level and contributor experience. Below, we present the full statistical results, robustness checks, diagnostic analyses, and descriptive summaries that underlie these findings.

% \subsection*{Subhead}
